body_text.text:
The qRT-PCR assay was first compared with the conventional RT-PCR (Ward et al., 1990) using extracted viral RNA. The presented DUGV assay was 3 log10
 FFU/mL more sensitive than the conventional RT-PCR (Fig. 1
). The qRT-PCR assay detected as low as 10 RNA copies/assay while the conventional RT-PCR detected 5.5 × 104 copies/assay, in our hands.
